## Imports, Aliases, and UI Barrels

### Aliases
- Use `$lib/*`, `$app/*`, `$env/*` paths (see [`knip.json`](mdc:knip.json)).

### UI barrels
- Import UI components from barrels to keep a clean API and exercise exports:
  - `import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "$lib/components/ui/card"`.
  - `import { Table, TableBody, TableCell, TableHead, TableHeader, TableRow } from "$lib/components/ui/table"`.
  - `import { Button } from "$lib/components/ui/button"`.
  - `import { DropdownMenuContent, DropdownMenuTrigger } from "$lib/components/ui/dropdown-menu"`.
  - `import { Badge } from "$lib/components/ui/badge"`.

### Conventions
- Avoid namespace imports; use named imports for tree-shaking.
- Prefer re-exported barrels over deep component paths for shared UI.
- Keep imports typed-only where appropriate to satisfy `verbatimModuleSyntax`.
